pageContext.claim: “Ambassador Kent -- who I have never had the privilege, I don't believe, of meeting; I don't know him -- and they brought him in as a witness against me, even though I don't know him. And he excoriated, from what they reported on the news -- and, of course, maybe, in this case, it won't be fake news -- but he excoriated the Obama administration and Joe Biden and Joe Biden's son, saying that he has tremendous problems, tremendous problems with Joe Biden's son and the Ukraine.”
pageContext.analysis: Deputy Assistant Secretary of State George Kent said he was concerned about the appearance of a conflict of interest, not that he had "tremendous problems" with the Bidens.
